name: Walgreens Pharmacy COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic - Watertown
description:
Please see below (or click on the ‘More Details’ button) for information about which groups are currently being vaccinated, how to schedule an appointment, and other important details about this vaccination location.

Site Name: Walgreens Pharmacy - Watertown
Address: 620 Main Street, Watertown, CT 06795
Vaccine Eligibility: Currently, only people ages 75+ are eligible to receive the vaccine at a retail pharmacy, such as Walgreens.
Scheduling: Sign in to your Walgreens.com account or log on to set up an account; Click on Account in upper right hand corner of website (It's free, quick and easy to create an account if you don’t have one.) Complete a short screening. If you’re eligible, choose a location and time for your COVID-19 vaccination appointment. If you’re receiving a two-dose vaccination, you can schedule your second dose after receiving your first vaccination. If you feel ill on the day of your vaccination, please reschedule your appointment when you feel healthy and well.

For your appointment, please arrive 15 minutes early and bring the following:
  • Your appointment confirmation email
  • Your COVID-19 Vaccination Authorization Form with your registration code (if applicable)
  • Your state ID, valid driver’s license or other government-issued ID
  • Your work ID or other document to show proof of employment (for healthcare workers, frontline and essential workers only)
  • Your medical and/or pharmacy benefit insurance card
  • Download, print and complete the vaccination consent form. If you don’t bring the completed form, you will need to complete it at the pharmacy before your vaccination.
eligibility: Currently, only people ages 75+ are eligible to receive the vaccine at a retail pharmacy, such as Walgreens.
application_process: Eligible individuals can schedule an appointment at this location online by clicking on the link: https://www.walgreens.com/topic/covid19vac/CT.jsp

description:

Vaccine Eligibility: Individuals ages 75+; Phase 1a-eligible individuals (healthcare providers and medical first responders). Click here for more details on groups included in Phase 1a.
Appointment Scheduling: Appointments are required for all vaccine recipients. Eligible individuals can schedule an appointment at this location online through the Vaccination Administration Management System (VAMS). Individuals can complete an enrollment form to gain access to VAMS to schedule themselves. The enrollment form and more information about the process can be found at https://portal.ct.gov/Coronavirus/COVID-19-Vaccinations---VAMS-Support. After the enrollment form is completed, individuals will receive an email from VAMS allowing them to log in and schedule a vaccine appointment (the email invitation for eligible individuals should arrive within 12 hours). To use VAMS, participants must have internet access and an email address.

Site Name: Bristol Hospital
Address: 41 Brewster Rd, Bristol, CT 06010
Hours: M-F: 8am-4pm (Appointment Required)
Vaccine Eligibility: Individuals ages 75+; Phase 1a-eligible individuals (healthcare providers and medical first responders). Click here for more details on groups included in Phase 1a.
Appointment Scheduling: Appointments are required for all vaccine recipients. Eligible individuals can schedule an appointment at this location online through the Vaccination Administration Management System (VAMS) or they can schedule it by calling 877-918-2224.
  • VAMS: Individuals can complete an enrollment form to gain access to VAMS to schedule themselves. The enrollment form and more information about this process can be found at https://portal.ct.gov/Coronavirus/COVID-19-Vaccinations---VAMS-Support. name: Pomperaug Health District COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic - Southbury (PDDH Office)
description:
Please see below (or click on the ‘More Details’ button) for information about which groups are currently being vaccinated, how to schedule an appointment, and other important details about this vaccination location.

Site Name: Pomperaug Health District
Address:77 Main Street North- Suite 205, Southbury, CT 06488
Vaccine Eligibility: Individuals ages 75+; Phase 1a-eligible individuals (healthcare providers and medical first responders). Click here for more details on groups included in Phase 1a.
Appointment Scheduling: Appointments are required for all vaccine recipients. Individuals can make an appointment at this location online at the health district's website or by phone.
  • Online: Individuals can visit the health district's website at https://www.pddh.org/programs/covid-19-vaccination.php and click on the link for 'Appointments for People 75 years & Older - at PDDH Office' to book an appointment through the website. New users will be prompted to create an account before they can use the online scheduling system.
  • Phone: Individuals without internet access can call 203-264-9616 (ext. 7) to make an appointment.
  • Second Dose Scheduling: Patients must schedule an appointment for a second dose at the time of their first vaccination.
What to Bring: Insurance card, completed consent form (link in confirmation email or a copy can be picked up at the office)
Access: This is a walk thru site requiring individuals to leave their vehicles. There are ramps into the building and elevator access to the 2nd floor.
Additional Information: Patients should arrive at the clinic 5 minutes ahead of their appointment and plan on being there for 30-45 minutes. There is a 15 minute observation time after receiving the vaccine.

name: Walgreens Pharmacy COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic - Torrington
description:
Please see below (or click on the ‘More Details’ button) for information about which groups are currently being vaccinated, how to schedule an appointment, and other important details about this vaccination location.

Site Name: Walgreens Pharmacy - Torrington
Address: 28 East Elm Street, Torrington, CT 06790
Vaccine Eligibility: Currently, only people ages 75+ are eligible to receive the vaccine at a retail pharmacy, such as Walgreens.
Scheduling: Sign in to your Walgreens.com account or log on to set up an account; Click on Account in upper right hand corner of website (It's free, quick and easy to create an account if you don’t have one.) Complete a short screening. If you’re eligible, choose a location and time for your COVID-19 vaccination appointment. If you’re receiving a two-dose vaccination, you can schedule your second dose after receiving your first vaccination. If you feel ill on the day of your vaccination, please reschedule your appointment when you feel healthy and well.

For your appointment, please arrive 15 minutes early and bring the following:
  • Your appointment confirmation email
  • Your COVID-19 Vaccination Authorization Form with your registration code (if applicable)
  • Your state ID, valid driver’s license or other government-issued ID
  • Your work ID or other document to show proof of employment (for healthcare workers, frontline and essential workers only)
  • Your medical and/or pharmacy benefit insurance card
  • Download, print and complete the vaccination consent form. If you don’t bring the completed form, you will need to complete it at the pharmacy before your vaccination.

description:

Site Name: New Britain High School
Address: 110 Mill Street, New Britain, CT 06051
Hours: Wednesdays: 10am-1pm (Appointment Required)
Vaccine Eligibility: Individuals ages 75+; Phase 1a-eligible individuals (healthcare providers and medical first responders). Click here for more details on groups included in Phase 1a.
Appointment Scheduling: Appointments are required for all vaccine recipients. Eligible individuals can schedule an appointment at this location online through the Vaccination Administration Management System (VAMS). Individuals can complete an enrollment form to gain access to VAMS to schedule themselves. The enrollment form and more information about the process can be found at https://portal.ct.gov/Coronavirus/COVID-19-Vaccinations---VAMS-Support. After the enrollment form is completed, individuals will receive an email from VAMS allowing them to log in and schedule a vaccine appointment (the email invitation for eligible individuals should arrive within 12 hours). To use VAMS, participants must have internet access and an email address.
What to Bring: Photo ID
Access: This is a walk thru site requiring individuals to leave their vehicles. Location has ADA accommodations for individuals with a disability.
Additional Information: This site is able to assist individuals that speak Spanish and Polish as well.

name: UCONN Health COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic
description:
Please see below (or click on the ‘More Details’ button) for information about which groups are currently being vaccinated, how to schedule an appointment, and other important details about this vaccination location.

Site Name: Uconn Health - John Dempsey Hospital
Address: 135 Dowling Way, Farmington 06030 (Outpatient Pavilion, 1st Floor)
Access: This is not a drive thru site. Individuals access the vaccination clinic on foot.
Vaccine Eligibility: Individuals ages 75+; Phase 1a-eligible individuals (healthcare providers and medical first responders). Click here for more information on who is currently eligible.
Appointment Scheduling: Individuals currently eligible for the vaccine may schedule an appointment at the UCONN Health vaccination clinic through MyChartPLUS. UCONN Health patients with an existing MyChartPLUS account can log into https://mychart.uconn.edu and click ‘SCHEDULE COVID VACCINE DOSE 1 FOR THOSE ELIGIBLE.' Eligible individuals without a MyChartPLUS account must first create an account and then they may schedule an appointment. Individuals needing help with scheduling an appointment at this location may call UCONN's dedicated COVID Vaccine Scheduling line at 860-679-5589. To create an account if you are not a current UCONN patient you can call 860-679-1600. For any MyChart questions or technical difficulties during regular business hours, contact 860-679-4400.
What to Bring: Proof of identification and insurance card
Accessibility: This is a walk thru site requiring individuals to leave their vehicles.
Additional Information: Individuals that need an interpreter service should notify this site of their language needs when making their appointment. Interpreters are available on site. ADA accommodations at this site include handicap accessible parking, ground level entrance, wheelchair offering, and automatic doors.

Vaccine Eligibility: Individuals ages 75+; Phase 1a individuals (healthcare personnel and medical first responders). Click here for more details on groups included in Phase 1a.
Appointment Scheduling: Appointments are required for all vaccine recipients. Eligible individuals can schedule an appointment at this location online through the Vaccination Administration Management System (VAMS) or they can schedule it by calling 877-918-2224.
  • VAMS: Individuals can complete an enrollment form to gain access to VAMS to schedule themselves. Additional Information: Individuals will need to remain on site for 15-30 minutes after the vaccine for monitoring.

name: Saint Francis Hospital COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic - Hartford (CIPCI)
description:
Please see below (or click on the ‘More Details’ button) for information about which groups are currently being vaccinated, how to schedule an appointment, and other important details about this vaccination location.

Site Name: Saint Francis Hospital - Connecticut Institute for Primary Care Innovation (CIPCI)
Address: CIPCI Building, 260 Ashley Street, 1st Floor, Hartford 06105
Vaccine Eligibility: Individuals ages 75+; Phase 1a-eligible individuals (healthcare providers and medical first responders). Click here for more details on groups included in Phase 1a.
Appointment Scheduling: Saint Francies is vaccinating Trinity Health of New England patients and non-patients.
  • Appointment Scheduling: Appointments are required for all vaccine recipients. Eligible individuals can schedule an appointment at this location online through the Vaccination Administration Management System (VAMS). Individuals can complete an enrollment form to gain access to VAMS to schedule themselves. The enrollment form and more information about the process can be found at https://portal.ct.gov/Coronavirus/COVID-19-Vaccinations---VAMS-Support. After the enrollment form is completed, individuals will receive an email from VAMS allowing them to log in and schedule a vaccine appointment (the email invitation for eligible individuals should arrive within 12 hours). To use VAMS, participants must have internet access and an email address.
  • Patient with Primary Care Doctor within Trinity Health of New England: Inform your primary care doctor that you are ready to be vaccinated. The doctor's office will need to participate in the CDC VAMS program so they can upload your information for registration. You will then receive an email invite from CDC VAMS to create an account and schedule an appointment.

One companion per patient is allowed for individuals who require mobility assistance or who have a disability. This locations uses a language service in order to be able to serve individuals who do not speak English.
Additional Information: Individuals should arrive no earlier than 30 minutes before appointment time. Patients should park in Lot C and check in with the security guard at the entrance of the parking lot. Masks, COVID-19 screening and temperature checks are required for all vaccine recipients.

Please see below (or click on the ‘More Details’ button) for information about which groups are currently being vaccinated, how to schedule an appointment, and other important details about this vaccination location.

Site Name: Trumbull COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic at Trumbull Senior Center
Address: 23 Priscilla Place, Trumbull, CT 06611
Vaccine Eligibility: Individuals ages 75+; Phase 1a-eligible individuals (healthcare providers and medical first responders). Click here for more details on groups included in Phase 1a.
Appointment Scheduling: Appointments are required for all vaccine recipients. Eligible individuals can schedule an appointment at this location online through the Vaccination Administration Management System (VAMS). Individuals can complete an enrollment form to gain access to VAMS to schedule themselves. The enrollment form and more information about the process can be found at https://portal.ct.gov/Coronavirus/COVID-19-Vaccinations---VAMS-Support. After the enrollment form is completed, individuals will receive an email from VAMS allowing them to log in and schedule a vaccine appointment (the email invitation for eligible individuals should arrive within 12 hours). To use VAMS, participants must have internet access and an email address.
Additional Information: The vaccine clinics at this location will generally be held on Tuesdays from 9am-3pm, depending on vaccine availability.

name: Community Health Center COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic - East Hartford (Pratt & Whitney Airfield) - Drive Thru
description:
Please see below (or click on the ‘More Details’ button) for information about which groups are currently being vaccinated, how to schedule an appointment, and other important details about this vaccination location.

Site Name: Community Health Center - COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic
Address: 12 Runway Road, East Hartford, CT 06118
Directions: Take East Hartford Boulevard North to Willow Street; (turn right in front of Cabela’s) to Runway Road on the left. Airfield entrance is on your left.
Hours: Mon-Sun: 8:30am-4pm (Appointment Required)
Vaccine Eligibility: Individuals ages 75+; Phase 1a individuals (healthcare personnel and medical first responders)
Appointment Scheduling: Appointments are required for all vaccine recipients. Eligible individuals can schedule an appointment at this location online through the Vaccination Administration Management System (VAMS) or they can schedule it by calling 877-918-2224.
  • VAMS: Individuals can complete an enrollment form to gain access to VAMS to schedule themselves. The enrollment form and more information about this process can be found at https://portal.ct.gov/Coronavirus/COVID-19-Vaccinations---VAMS-Support. After the enrollment form is completed, individuals will receive an email from VAMS allowing them to log in and schedule a vaccine appointment (the email invitation for eligible individuals should arrive within 12 hours). To use VAMS, participants must have internet access and an email address.
  • Phone: Individuals can schedule an appointment at this location by phone by dialing the CT COVID-19 Vaccine Appointment Assist Line at 877-918-2224.
Access: This is a drive thru site requiring individuals to be in a vehicle. Individuals being driven to the site should sit in the rear seat on the driver side so that the provider can vaccinate the left arm, unless they have a need for the right arm to be vaccinated.
Additional Information: Individuals will need to remain on site for 15-30 minutes after the vaccine for monitoring.

name: Saint Vincent's Medical Center COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic
description:
Please see below (or click on the ‘More Details’ button) for information about which groups are currently being vaccinated, how to schedule an appointment, and other important details about this vaccination location.

Site Name: Saint Vincent's Medical Center
Address: 2800 Main Street, Bridgeport, CT 06606
Vaccine Eligibility: Individuals ages 75+; Phase 1a-eligible individuals only (healthcare providers and medical first responders). Click here for more details on groups included in Phase 1a.
Scheduling: Individuals currently eligible for the vaccine may schedule an appointment at a Hartford Healthcare vaccination clinic through MyChartPLUS. Hartford Healthcare patients with an existing MyChartPLUS account can log into mychartplus.org and click ‘Schedule an Appointment’, which is listed under ‘Visits’ at the top. Eligible individuals without a MyChartPLUS account must first create an account and then they may schedule an appointment. If you'd prefer to schedule your appointment by phone, call the Hartford HealthCare Access Center at 860-827-7690 or toll-free at 833-943-5721. The Access Center is available M-F: 8am-5pm. For questions or assistance with scheduling appointments through MyChartPLUS, please call 860-972-4993.

name: Walgreens Pharmacy COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic - Canaan
description:
Please see below (or click on the ‘More Details’ button) for information about which groups are currently being vaccinated, how to schedule an appointment, and other important details about this vaccination location.

Site Name: Walgreens Pharmacy - Canaan
Address: 76 Main Street, Canaan, CT 06018
Vaccine Eligibility: Currently, only people ages 75+ are eligible to receive the vaccine at a retail pharmacy, such as Walgreens.
Scheduling: Sign in to your Walgreens.com account or log on to set up an account; Click on Account in upper right hand corner of website (It's free, quick and easy to create an account if you don’t have one.) Complete a short screening. If you’re eligible, choose a location and time for your COVID-19 vaccination appointment. If you’re receiving a two-dose vaccination, you can schedule your second dose after receiving your first vaccination. If you feel ill on the day of your vaccination, please reschedule your appointment when you feel healthy and well.

For your appointment, please arrive 15 minutes early and bring the following:
  • Your appointment confirmation email
  • Your COVID-19 Vaccination Authorization Form with your registration code (if applicable)
  • Your state ID, valid driver’s license or other government-issued ID
  • Your work ID or other document to show proof of employment (for healthcare workers, frontline and essential workers only)
  • Your medical and/or pharmacy benefit insurance card
  • Download, print and complete the vaccination consent form. If you don’t bring the completed form, you will need to complete it at the pharmacy before your vaccination.
eligibility: Currently, only people ages 75+ are eligible to receive the vaccine at a retail pharmacy, such as Walgreens.
application_process: Eligible individuals can schedule an appointment at this location online by clicking on the link: https://www.walgreens.com/topic/covid19vac/CT.jsp

Vaccine Eligibility: Individuals ages 75+; Phase 1a-eligible individuals (healthcare providers and medical first responders). Click here for more details on groups included in Phase 1a.
Scheduling: Johnson Memorial is vaccinating Trinity Health of New England patients and non-patients.

  • Appointment Scheduling: Appointments are required for all vaccine recipients. Eligible individuals can schedule an appointment at this location online through the Vaccination Administration Management System (VAMS). Individuals can complete an enrollment form to gain access to VAMS to schedule themselves. The enrollment form and more information about the process can be found at https://portal.ct.gov/Coronavirus/COVID-19-Vaccinations---VAMS-Support. After the enrollment form is completed, individuals will receive an email from VAMS allowing them to log in and schedule a vaccine appointment (the email invitation for eligible individuals should arrive within 12 hours). To use VAMS, participants must have internet access and an email address.
  • Patient with Primary Care Doctor within Trinity Health of New England: Inform your primary care doctor that you are ready to be vaccinated. The doctor's office will need to participate in the CDC VAMS program so they can upload your information for registration. You will then receive an email invite from CDC VAMS to create an account and schedule an appointment.
What to Bring: Photo ID and insurance card
Accessibility: This is a walk thru site requiring individuals to leave their vehicles. Location has ADA accommodations including elevators and wheelchairs for individuals with limited mobility. ASL translation services are available for hard of hearing. Marrti language services are available for non-English speakers. One companion per patient is allowed for individuals who require mobility assistance or who have a disability.
Additional Information: Individuals should arrive no earlier than 30 minutes before appointment time. Individuals can park in the main parking lot, check in at the Information Desk, and take the elevator to the third floor for the vaccine clinic. Masks, COVID-19 screening and temperature checks are required for all vaccine recipients.

name: Walgreens Pharmacy COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic - Stafford Springs
description:
Please see below (or click on the ‘More Details’ button) for information about which groups are currently being vaccinated, how to schedule an appointment, and other important details about this vaccination location.

Site Name: Walgreens Pharmacy - Stafford Springs
Address: 88 West Stafford Road, Stafford Springs, CT 06076
Vaccine Eligibility: Currently, only people ages 75+ are eligible to receive the vaccine at a retail pharmacy, such as Walgreens.
Scheduling: Sign in to your Walgreens.com account or log on to set up an account; Click on Account in upper right hand corner of website (It's free, quick and easy to create an account if you don’t have one.) Complete a short screening. If you’re eligible, choose a location and time for your COVID-19 vaccination appointment. If you’re receiving a two-dose vaccination, you can schedule your second dose after receiving your first vaccination. If you feel ill on the day of your vaccination, please reschedule your appointment when you feel healthy and well.

For your appointment, please arrive 15 minutes early and bring the following:
  • Your appointment confirmation email
  • Your COVID-19 Vaccination Authorization Form with your registration code (if applicable)
  • Your state ID, valid driver’s license or other government-issued ID
  • Your work ID or other document to show proof of employment (for healthcare workers, frontline and essential workers only)
  • Your medical and/or pharmacy benefit insurance card
  • Download, print and complete the vaccination consent form. If you don’t bring the completed form, you will need to complete it at the pharmacy before your vaccination.

Eligible individuals can schedule an appointment at this location online through the Vaccination Administration Management System (VAMS). The Senior Center is an ADA Compliant facility, single level, wheelchair accessible.

name: Walgreens Pharmacy COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic - Canterbury
description:
Please see below (or click on the ‘More Details’ button) for information about which groups are currently being vaccinated, how to schedule an appointment, and other important details about this vaccination location.

Site Name: Walgreens Pharmacy - Canterbury
Address: 200 Westminster Road, Canterbury, CT 06331
Vaccine Eligibility: Currently, only people ages 75+ are eligible to receive the vaccine at a retail pharmacy, such as Walgreens.
Scheduling: Sign in to your Walgreens.com account or log on to set up an account; Click on Account in upper right hand corner of website (It's free, quick and easy to create an account if you don’t have one.) Complete a short screening. If you’re eligible, choose a location and time for your COVID-19 vaccination appointment. If you’re receiving a two-dose vaccination, you can schedule your second dose after receiving your first vaccination. If you feel ill on the day of your vaccination, please reschedule your appointment when you feel healthy and well.

For your appointment, please arrive 15 minutes early and bring the following:
  • Your appointment confirmation email
  • Your COVID-19 Vaccination Authorization Form with your registration code (if applicable)
  • Your state ID, valid driver’s license or other government-issued ID
  • Your work ID or other document to show proof of employment (for healthcare workers, frontline and essential workers only)
  • Your medical and/or pharmacy benefit insurance card
  • Download, print and complete the vaccination consent form. If you don’t bring the completed form, you will need to complete it at the pharmacy before your vaccination.

To use VAMS, participants must have internet access and an email address.

Additional Information: Online language services only available.

name: Walgreens Pharmacy COVID-19 Vaccine Clinic - Dayville
description:
Please see below (or click on the ‘More Details’ button) for information about which groups are currently being vaccinated, how to schedule an appointment, and other important details about this vaccination location.

Site Name: Walgreens Pharmacy - Dayville
Address: 1093 North Main Street, Dayville, CT 06241
Vaccine Eligibility: Currently, only people ages 75+ are eligible to receive the vaccine at a retail pharmacy, such as Walgreens.
Scheduling: Sign in to your Walgreens.com account or log on to set up an account; Click on Account in upper right hand corner of website (It's free, quick and easy to create an account if you don’t have one.) Complete a short screening. If you’re eligible, choose a location and time for your COVID-19 vaccination appointment. If you’re receiving a two-dose vaccination, you can schedule your second dose after receiving your first vaccination. If you feel ill on the day of your vaccination, please reschedule your appointment when you feel healthy and well.

For your appointment, please arrive 15 minutes early and bring the following:
  • Your appointment confirmation email
  • Your COVID-19 Vaccination Authorization Form with your registration code (if applicable)
  • Your state ID, valid driver’s license or other government-issued ID
  • Your work ID or other document to show proof of employment (for healthcare workers, frontline and essential workers only)
  • Your medical and/or pharmacy benefit insurance card
  • Download, print and complete the vaccination consent form. If you don’t bring the completed form, you will need to complete it at the pharmacy before your vaccination.
